# 5. あの頃の私は

Oikawa: You wouldn't believe how dazzling she was back then. She was just like Hagiyama. No, even more brilliant...
Shizuku: (Mr. Oikawa said I used to have a dazzling aura when I was still with Cheerful * Days...)
Shizuku: (It's why he asked me to audition.)
Shizuku: (And yet, I haven't been able to live up to his expectations...)
Shizuku: (If things continue like this, then in the worst case scenario, I might get dropped from the commercial entirely.)
Shizuku: (I have to stop that from happening.)
Shizuku: (But is it even possible for me to regain the aura I once had...?)
Shizuku: How would I go about doing that...?
Shizuku: I know...
Shizuku: (I might be able to learn something by watching videos of myself from back then.)
Shizuku: There should be some of me practicing on my own saved to my tablet—
???: <Shizuku!>
Shizuku: Eep!
Shizuku: Oh, Miku, it's you... What brings you here all of a sudden?
Miku: <I'm sorry if I startled you! But I came to ask about your fitting session, since you said it was today.>
Miku: <That Hagiyama girl was also there, right? So, how did everything go?>
Shizuku: Oh, so... I'd say it went well, since I had a chance to hear about her thought process and resolve.
Shizuku: Also...
Shizuku: I learned something else.
Miku: <...?>
Miku: <I see... And this Mr. Oikawa really said that...?>
Shizuku: Yes.
Shizuku: Which is why I was thinking about watching some videos of myself, to discover the truth behind what that “aura” of mine was.
Miku: <I see...>
Miku: <In that case, Shizuku, would it be alright if we watched together?>
Miku: <Not only should having an extra set of eyes help you solve this problem, I'd like to learn more about the old you.>
Shizuku: Miku...
Shizuku: Thank you. Then, let's watch together, shall we?
Miku: <Okay!>
Shizuku: I'll try playing it now. Pressing this button should turn the power on...
Shizuku: Huh? It isn't lighting up for some reason...
Miku: <Oh... Could its battery have run out?>
Shizuku: Yes, you might be right! Let's see... The charger for it should be...
Shizuku: Thank you for being so patient, Miku. I should be able to play it now.
Miku: <Great...!>
Miku: <Is this you doing dance practice?>
Shizuku: Yes. I think I took it to make sure my form looked okay.
Shizuku: This really takes me back... This was the first song I learned after becoming the lead.
Miku: <Really...?!>
Miku: <Hehe. It's obvious that you're trying your very best.>
Miku: <Oh, but...>
Miku: <You also seem a little worried.>
Shizuku: Yes, you're right...
Shizuku: Back then, I wasn't sure if I'd do a good job as the lead. I'm sure that worry showed clearly on my face.
Miku: <Right... That reminds me of what you said about having to struggle for a little while.>
Shizuku: Yes, because I felt that I didn't have the skills or mindset the role demanded of me.
Shizuku: I feel so embarrassed looking back now...
Shizuku: I'm struggling to keep up with the song, and every motion I take looks so unrefined...
Miku: <Yes, I can see why the current you would feel that way.>
Miku: <But I'm seeing more than just that.>
Shizuku: Huh?
Shizuku: <No... This isn't good enough...>
Shizuku: <I know I can do much better...>
Shizuku: <I have to...!!>
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Shizuku: Just now, for a second there...
Shizuku: I didn't recognize myself.
Miku: <Yes, but...>
Miku: <This girl is also you, Shizuku.>
Shizuku: What...?
Miku: <Tell me, Shizuku. What was going through your mind during this practice?>
Shizuku: During this one? Umm...
Shizuku: I felt that I had to absolutely shine when I performed this dance...
Shizuku: I kept telling myself that I had to succeed no matter what.
Miku: <Ah, I had a feeling.>
Miku: <Looking at your eyes here, Shizuku, I can tell that there's strong resolve at work here.>
Shizuku: Strong resolve...?
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: (She's right...)
Shizuku: (Back then, I was much more...)
Shizuku: Thank you, Miku...
Shizuku: This conversation has helped remind me of how I really felt back then.
Shizuku: Back then, I was constantly worried about how I'd actually do as the lead. But...
Shizuku: It's also why I was so desperate.
Shizuku: *Sigh*
Manager: Shizuku, you have to get to your next appointment. How are you feeling? Good...?
Shizuku: Oh, yes... It's that magazine interview, correct? I've made sure to memorize all the answers to their questions, so I should be more than ready for it.
Manager: Okay, but... In the event that they do decide to throw you a curveball, Arisa will be there to help. So, feel free to ask for assistance whenever.
Shizuku: Okay...
Shizuku: (This isn't good...)
Shizuku: (The lead is supposed to be a group's central pillar.)
Shizuku: (But I'm always making everyone worry... I'm always having to ask for their help...)
Shizuku: (Doesn't that mean I'm not really cut out for...?)
???: Oh! Hi, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Huh? Oh...
???: Good morning, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Hang on... You're all going to be joining Cheerful * Days soon, yes? The others told me the news.
Junior Idol: Yes! Starting next month, we'll be joining you for lessons!
Junior Idol: A-And... I'm so happy about getting to join Cheerful * Days...!
Shizuku: Huh?
Junior Idol: Cheerful * Days is the reason I love idols so much...! I've been doing everything I can in order to become an amazing performer like you and the others!
Junior Idol: We look forward to working with you, and we promise to do our very best in order to not let you all down!
Shizuku: Yes, I look forward to working with all of you as well.
Shizuku: (Their eyes are so beautiful...)
Shizuku: (They look so honest and pure... I can tell that they've worked very hard to get here...)
Shizuku: (Which means...)
Shizuku: (I'm the lead now, so I'm responsible for these girls' futures.)
Shizuku: (I can't show any weakness in front of them.)
Shizuku: (As terrifying it is that I'm responsible for this group's future...)
Shizuku: (I have to keep practicing. Regardless of how scared I am.)
Shizuku: (I have to keep finding ways to improve...!)
Shizuku: (I have to lead Cheerful * Days to the top and clear a path towards a bright future for us all!)
Miku: <That really happened...?>
Shizuku: Yes. Between my responsibilities and the quality which was expected of me, I ended up struggling quite a lot...
Shizuku: But that pressure and the expectations placed on me also pushed me to become better.
Miku: <Which would explain why you're shining so much in this video...>
Shizuku: Yes...
Shizuku: I've been coddling myself since joining MORE MORE JUMP!
Miku: <What?>
Shizuku: The others, as well as our fans, have accepted me for “who I really am”.
Shizuku: I'm standing here now because of their kindness. But if you look at the other side of that coin...
Shizuku: You'll see a person who thinks she doesn't need to work hard on her own. Because those around her have told her that it's okay to lean on your friends...
Shizuku: I've become so accustomed to this new environment that I've allowed myself to become soft.
Shizuku: It's no wonder that Mr. Oikawa thinks I've lost my aura...
Shizuku: I don't have to lead our group. I don't feel compelled to shine brighter than my peers. I don't have that strong resolve anymore.
Miku: <Shizuku...>
Miku: <But if you know all this now, then there's only one thing left to do!>
Shizuku: Yes, that's right.
Shizuku: I have to regain what I had before— No, I need to face this job with even greater resolve than that.
Shizuku: It's my turn to lead MORE MORE JUMP! I have to make the commitment to become better than ever, no matter what.
Shizuku: I'm going to shine brighter than everyone else, and blow Mr. Oikawa and the others away...
Shizuku: I will succeed...!
Shizuku: Thank you for your help, Miku. I know exactly what I need to do now.
Miku: <That's great to hear!>
Miku: <I'll be looking forward to seeing your commercial, Shizuku!>
Shizuku: Thank you!
